,"Abt 1250":"circa 1250","1259":"1259","1226":"1226","1314":"1314","1244":"1244","Abt 1275":"circa 1275","1276":"1276","6 May 1307":"6 mei 1307","25 December 1273 (age 33 1306-07)":"25 december 1273","after 1276":"na 1276","1219":"1219","1307":"1307","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Brampton Bierlow, Yorkshire, England":"Brampton Bierlow, Yorkshire, England","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England"},"en":{"Abt 1250–6 May 1307":"about 1250–6 May 1307","1242–Male":"1242–Deceased","1244–Male":"1244–Deceased","1250–1307":"1250–1307","1240–Female":"1240–Deceased","1273–1314":"1273–1314","1275–1351":"1275–1351","1219–1274":"1219–1274","1226–1276":"1226–1276","1275":"1275","1242":"1242","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Abt 1274":"about 1274","Abt 1250":"about 1250","1259":"1259","1226":"1226","1314":"1314","1244":"1244","Abt 1275":"about 1275","1276":"1276","6 May 1307":"6 May 1307","25 December 1273 (age 33 1306-07)":"25 December 1273","after 1276":"after 1276","1219":"1219","1307":"1307","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Brampton Bierlow, Yorkshire, England":"Brampton Bierlow, Yorkshire, England","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fleming","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, from Middle English <i>fleming</i>. The word reflects a Norman French form of Old French <i>flamanc</i> ‘Fleming’, from the stem <i>flam-</i> + the ancient Germanic suffix <i>-ing</i>. In the Middle Ages there was considerable commercial intercourse between England and the Netherlands, particularly in the wool trade, and many Flemish weavers and dyers settled in England. This surname is also common in south and east Scotland and in Ireland, where it is sometimes found in the Gaelicized form <b>Pléamonn</b>.","German: variant of   Flemming  , cognate with 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Flemings","meanings":["English: plural form of   Fleming  .","Americanized form of Flemish <b>Vleminckx</b>: patronymic from <b>Vleminck</b>, an ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle Dutch <i>vleminc</i>."]},{"name":"Flanders","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Middle English <i>Fla(u)ndres</i> ‘Flanders’, denoting someone from Flanders, a historical region covering parts of modern-day Belgium, France, and the Netherlands. Compare   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Fleeman","meanings":["English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flemming","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flamenco","meanings":["Spanish: ethnic name from <i>flamenco</i> ‘Fleming, Flemish person’ (see   Fleming  )."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":9,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":40,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Fleming III was born about 1250, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Reyner Fleming III, was 33 and his mother, Rosamund Horbury, was 26. He had at least 2 sons with Alice. He died on 6 May 1307, in Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 58."},"et":{"Abt 1250–6 May 1307":"umbes 1250–6. mai 1307","1242–Male":"1242–Surnud","1244–Male":"1244–Surnud","1250–1307":"1250–1307","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1273–1314":"1273–1314","1275–1351":"1275–1351","1219–1274":"1219–1274","1226–1276":"1226–1276","1275":"1275","1242":"1242","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Abt 1274":"umbes 1274","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","1259":"1259","1226":"1226","1314":"1314","1244":"1244","Abt 1275":"umbes 1275","1276":"1276","6 May 1307":"6. mai 1307","25 December 1273 (age 33 1306-07)":"25. detsember 1273","after 1276":"pärast 1276","1219":"1219","1307":"1307","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Brampton Bierlow, Yorkshire, England":"Brampton Bierlow, Yorkshire, England","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1250–6 May 1307":"noin 1250–6. toukokuuta 1307","1242–Male":"1242–Kuollut","1244–Male":"1244–Kuollut","1250–1307":"1250–1307","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1273–1314":"1273–1314","1275–1351":"1275–1351","1219–1274":"1219–1274","1226–1276":"1226–1276","1275":"1275","1242":"1242","1274":"1274","1351":"1351","1273":"1273","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1290":"1290","Abt 1274":"noin 1274","Abt 1250":"noin 